Du &amp; jag d&lt;U+00F6&gt;den (Swedish for &quot;You &amp; I Death&quot;) is a 2005 album by the Swedish band Kent. As the title implies, death is a major theme of the album which before its release was described by the band as dark and depressing.
The album sold more than 200 000 copies in Scandinavia during the weeks following its March 15 release. Three singles were released from the album: Max 500, Palace &amp; Main and Den d&lt;U+00F6&gt;da vinkeln.
