Du &lt;U+00E4&gt;r &lt;U+00E5&gt;nga (You are vapor)
Den d&lt;U+00F6&gt;da vinkeln (The dead angle)
Du var min arm&lt;U+00E9&gt; (You were my army)
Palace &amp; Main (J.Berg/M.Sk&lt;U+00F6&gt;ld)
J&lt;U+00E4&gt;rnsp&lt;U+00F6&gt;ken (Iron ghosts)*
Kl&lt;U+00E5&gt;paren (The klutz) (J.Berg/M.Sk&lt;U+00F6&gt;ld)
Max 500
Romeo &lt;U+00E5&gt;terv&lt;U+00E4&gt;nder ensam (Romeo returns alone) (J.Berg/M.Sk&lt;U+00F6&gt;ld)
Rosor &amp; palmblad (Roses &amp; palmleaves)
Mannen i den vita hatten (16 &lt;U+00E5&gt;r senare) (The man in the white hat (16 years later))
The song name &quot;J&lt;U+00E4&gt;rnsp&lt;U+00F6&gt;ken&quot; plays on an expression in Swedish, &quot;Hj&lt;U+00E4&gt;rnsp&lt;U+00F6&gt;ken&quot;, which means imaginary ghosts, or ghosts in one's brain. &quot;Hj&lt;U+00E4&gt;rna&quot; is Swedish for &quot;brain&quot;, whereas &quot;J&lt;U+00E4&gt;rn&quot; means &quot;iron&quot;, but the two words are pronounced the same way.
Other info
The plastic album cover and the playable side of the CD is black.
A limited edition of the CD was also available. This included postcards sensitive to UV-light, a booklet printed on especially thin paper and a poster with the cover picture, among other things. The limitation was 9000 items.
The album was also available on vinyl, limited to 1500 items.
